  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the investigators study is to compare in children aged less than 18 months and
      hospitalized for an acute viral bronchiolitis the efficacy of the HS 3% (Mucoclear®, sterile
      ampoules of 4 ml) nebulised with a conventional jet-nebulizer (particles diameter of 4-5 µm),
      or with a jet-nebulizer adapted for infants (particles diameter of 2-2.5 µm), or with a
      mesh-nebulizer adapted for infants (particles diameter of 2-2.5 µm).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
